ortItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529124\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529124\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kar1665702528238.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kar1665702528238.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kar1665702528238.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kar1665702528238\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">/altnet\n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Allow Uniface to use the network connector specified by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dnp</span> switch, even if it is different than the one used to originally connect to the Uniface Router.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kar1665702528238__topic_d138875e1_d138876e1_d138877e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138878e1_d138879e1_d138880e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/altnet</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kar1665702528238__section_nvg_z2v_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d776532e63\"> Use </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138884e1_d138885e1_d138886e1\">Use with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dnp</span> switch in the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">userver</code> command lines defined in the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface\n        Router assignment file.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kar1665702528238__section_snk_bfv_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d776532e78\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138890e1_d138891e1_d138892e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/altnet</span> switch when the\n        connector specified by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dnp</span> switch is different to the one used by\n        the client to connect to the Uniface Router.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kar1665702528238__section_bpx_dfv_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d776532e93\"> Example: Enabling the use of Multiple Network Connectors </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138896e1_d138897e1_d138898e1\">The client assignment file contains the following\n        settings for connecting to a Uniface Server:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kar1665702528238__pre_wxr_hfv_yvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;client.asn\n[NET_SETTINGS]\nSrv1Cert verify_server=yes, ca_cert=usys:myca1.crt <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#kar1665702528238__list_item_1\">1</a>\n\n[PATHS]\n$SRV1 TLS:server1.mydomain+13002:Srv1Cert|user|password|MyUst <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#kar1665702528238__list_item_2\">2</a> \n         </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138899e1_d138900e1_d138901e1\">The assignment file of the Uniface Router contains the\n        following settings:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kar1665702528238__pre_byr_hfv_yvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; urouter.asn\n[NET_SETTINGS]\nSrv1Cert verify_server=yes, srv_cert=usys:myserver1.crt, %/\n srv_key=usys:myserver1.key <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#kar1665702528238__list_item_1\">1</a>\n\n[SERVERS]\nMyUST=userver.exe /asn=userver.asn /dnp=TCP:+13001 <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#kar1665702528238__list_item_3\">3</a> /altnet <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#kar1665702528238__list_item_4\">4</a>\n         </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kar1665702528238__p_d138902e1_d138903e1_d138904e1\">To use both the TCP and TLS connector, the Uniface\n        Router must be started from the command line to listen on two ports. (It is not possible to\n        specify multiple listening ports using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_NET</span>. ) For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kar1665702528238__pre_fyr_hfv_yvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">urouter TLS:+13001:Srv1Cert TCP:+13001</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"kar1665702528238__ol_att_q3v_yvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kar1665702528238__list_item_1\">The TLS connection profile enables server verification, so this is\n          specified in both the client and Uniface Router assignment files. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kar1665702528238__list_item_2\">The connection profile <code class=\"ph codeph\">Srv1Cert</code> is used to define the\n          connection parameters for the TLS connector. The profile name must be the same in both the\n          client and Uniface Router assignment files, and the profile must match, so that the CA\n          certificate on the client verifies server certificate and public key of the Uniface\n          Router. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kar1665702528238__list_item_3\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/dnp</span> path uses the insecure TCP driver. This\n          means the connection between the Uniface Router and the Uniface Server will not be\n          encrypted or otherwise secured.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kar1665702528238__list_item_4\">Because the default connector and the connector for the Uniface Server\n          are not the same, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/altnet</span> switch must also specified. </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jin1665702525125.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/dnp</a><p>Register a client application or Uniface Server under a symbolic name with a Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529124\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529124\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/altnet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /altnet Allow Uniface to use the network connector specified by the /dnp switch, even if it is different than the one used to originally connect to the Uniface Router. /altnet Use Use with the /dnp switch in the userver command lines defined in the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router assignment file. Description Use the /altnet switch when the connector specified by the /dnp switch is different to the one used by the client to connect to the Uniface Router. Example: Enabling the use of Multiple Network Connectors The client assignment file contains the following settings for connecting to a Uniface Server: ;client.asn [NET_SETTINGS] Srv1Cert verify_server=yes, ca_cert=usys:myca1.crt 1 [PATHS] $SRV1 TLS:server1.mydomain+13002:Srv1Cert|user|password|MyUst 2 Copy The assignment file of the Uniface Router contains the following settings: ; urouter.asn [NET_SETTINGS] Srv1Cert verify_server=yes, srv_cert=usys:myserver1.crt, %/ srv_key=usys:myserver1.key 1 [SERVERS] MyUST=userver.exe /asn=userver.asn /dnp=TCP:+13001 3 /altnet 4 Copy To use both the TCP and TLS connector, the Uniface Router must be started from the command line to listen on two ports. (It is not possible to specify multiple listening ports using $DEFAULT_NET . ) For example: urouter TLS:+13001:Srv1Cert TCP:+13001 Copy The TLS connection profile enables server verification, so this is specified in both the client and Uniface Router assignment files. The connection profile Srv1Cert is used to define the connection parameters for the TLS connector. The profile name must be the same in both the client and Uniface Router assignment files, and the profile must match, so that the CA certificate on the client verifies server certificate and public key of the Uniface Router. The /dnp path uses the insecure TCP driver. This means the connection between the Uniface Router and the Uniface Server will not be encrypted or otherwise secured. Because the default connector and the connector for the Uniface Server are not the same, the /altnet switch must also specified. Related Links /dnp Register a client application or Uniface Server under a symbolic name with a Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}